;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2666+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F21%2F34%2Fe956519446c783cfd6105da63120%2Fgettyimages-2222755407-2.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2666+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F21%2F34%2Fe956519446c783cfd6105da63120%2Fgettyimages-2222755407-2.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2666+0+0/resize/1000/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F21%2F34%2Fe956519446c783cfd6105da63120%2Fgettyimages-2222755407-2.jpg 1000w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2666+0+0/resize/1300/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F21%2F34%2Fe956519446c783cfd6105da63120%2Fgettyimages-2222755407-2.jpg 1300w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2666+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F21%2F34%2Fe956519446c783cfd6105da63120%2Fgettyimages-2222755407-2.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2666+0+0/resize/2000/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F21%2F34%2Fe956519446c783cfd6105da63120%2Fgettyimages-2222755407-2.jpg 2000w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2666+0+0/resize/2600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F21%2F34%2Fe956519446c783cfd6105da63120%2Fgettyimages-2222755407-2.jpg 2600w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2666+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F21%2F34%2Fe956519446c783cfd6105da63120%2Fgettyimages-2222755407-2.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 1238px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 60px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 60px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2666+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F21%2F34%2Fe956519446c783cfd6105da63120%2Fgettyimages-2222755407-2.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2666+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F21%2F34%2Fe956519446c783cfd6105da63120%2Fgettyimages-2222755407-2.jpg" class="img" alt="Residents inspect the damage following a Russian air strike in a residential area of Kyiv, Ukraine." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Residents inspect the damage following a Russian air strike in a residential area of Kyiv, Ukraine.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Andrew Kravchenko/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Zelenskyy also claimed that he and Trump had a agreed on a meeting of their teams. "We are ready for direct projects with America and believe that this is extremely necessary for security, especially with regard to drones and related technologies," he added.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;That phone call came one day after Trump &lt;a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2025/07/03/us/politics/trump-putin-call-ukraine-iran.html?searchResultPosition=1" target="_blank"&gt;spoke with Putin&lt;/a&gt; about ending the war in Ukraine. Trump said he was "very disappointed" with the conversation.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;"I didn't make any progress with him today at all," he said, adding "I'm not happy about that."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resnx-s1-5456846-101" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col"&gt;                     &lt;!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" --&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!-- END ID="RESNX-S1-5456846-101" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " --&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The Kremlin's foreign affairs adviser Yuri Ushakov, said Putin told Trump that Russia will not back down in trying to achieve its goals in Ukraine, and that the war will continue until Moscow gets to the "root causes" of the conflict.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Ushakov did not explain what Putin's goals in Ukraine were, but the Russian leader has said in the past that he wants Ukraine to forfeit territory and refrain from joining military alliances such as NATO.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
